*"Bulldozers roll in Bareilly: House linked to Tauqeer Raza sealed, Nafees Ahmed's 'Raja Palace' demolished"*

_Authorities intensified their crackdown in Bareilly, taking strong action against properties connected to recent violence and key local figures._

*Read more:* [https://toi.in/vJvW9a55]
extendedTextMessage.description:
Following the recent clashes, the district administration on Saturday carried out a demolition drive against illegal constructions in several parts of the city.

On Saturday morning, Raza Palace, a marriage hall owned by Dr Nafees Ahmed in the Jakhira area, was demolished by Bareilly Development Authority teams in the presence of a heavy police force.

Officials said the action was taken due to violations of building norms.

The nameplate at the site identified the property owner as Mutawalli Shoaib Beg, son of the late Athar Beg, a former PCS officer.

In Faik Enclave, the administration sealed a house belonging to Farhat, where Maulana Tauqeer Raza was allegedly sheltered during the recent violence.
